HEADWORD: Polyautography
<hw>Pol`y*au*tog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> + <ets>autography</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act or
practice of multiplying copies of one's own handwriting, or of
manuscripts, by printing from stone, -- a species of
lithography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polybasic</ent>⟦br⟧
